==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: imprinting
<hw>im*print"ing</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Ethology,
Psychology)</fld> <def>The learning of a behavioral pattern that occurs
soon after birth or hatching in certain animals, in which a long-lasting
response to an individual (such as a parent) or an object is rapidly
acquired; it is particularly noted in the response of certain birds to
the animal they first see after hatching, usually the parent, as in
ducks who will follow the adult duck they first see.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Imprison</ent>⟦br⟧
